# aa0d053760864c6dac605dc9f5cfa14a
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:37
msgid ""
"The Apache Traffic Server API enables you to create plugins, using the C "
"programming language, that customize the behavior of your Traffic Server "
"installation."
msgstr ""

# 8a11c8ac26ff4bf8acc349c1c67ecaad
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:41
msgid ""
"Traffic Server enables sophisticated caching and processing of web-"
"related traffic, such as DNS and HTTP requests and responses. Traffic "
"Server itself consists of an event-driven loop that can be simplified as "
"follows::"
msgstr ""

# 56e68dd15a694ae68c10070097fd1ea5
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:51
msgid ""
"You compile your plugin source code to create a shared library that "
"Traffic Server loads when it is started. Your plugin contains callback "
"functions that are registered for specific Traffic Server events. When "
"Traffic Server needs to process an event, it invokes any and all call-"
"back functions you've registered for that event type."
msgstr ""

# e63b929e79114feaaac1ac03c5f8aaf1
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:58
msgid "Possible uses for plugins include the following:"
msgstr ""

# f68fefe897e9432b9d11d0360cbc1a69
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:60
msgid ""
"HTTP processing plugins can filter, blacklist, authorize users or "
"transform content."
msgstr ""

# fc4bdfe668834eb38890dfc9d6937f73
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:62
msgid ""
"Protocol plugins can enable Traffic Server to proxy-cache new protocol "
"content."
msgstr ""

# 0c92b5b4a55841bbb57463559eca51ba
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:64
msgid ""
"A blacklisting plugin denies attempts to access web sites that are off-"
"limits."
msgstr ""

# b586b6c2d76e4d43aaeedb0504167cbe
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:66
msgid "Append transform plugins add data to HTTP response content."
msgstr ""

# b85c371bd7164ef49b76b776a464c094
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:68
msgid "An image conversion plugin transforms JPEG images to GIF images."
msgstr ""

# 961204b7fe7443b58d1e565de22b1d54
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:70
msgid ""
"Compression plugins send response content to a compression server that "
"compresses the data (alternatively, a compression library local to the "
"Traffic Server host machine could do the compression)."
msgstr ""

# b96c141cc53144e58a8dfeb1d2aa1ef8
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:74
msgid ""
"Authorization plugins check a user's permissions to access particular web"
" sites. The plugin could consult a local authorization program or send "
"queries to an authorization server."
msgstr ""

# 223a361ff1024c419cdaea9d65a42e64
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:78
msgid ""
"A plugin that gathers client information from request headers and enters "
"this information in a database."
msgstr ""

# 73e048fea27e455cbf755b5f4c552392
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:81
msgid ""
"A protocol plugin listen for specific protocol requests on a designated "
"port and then uses Traffic Server's proxy server and cache to serve "
"client requests."
msgstr ""

# 018dd50a5963441d8c8dfc59156adb2a
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:88
msgid "Naming Conventions"
msgstr ""

# f12480b2c9c847f89035167851bbf19f
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:90
msgid "The Traffic Server API adheres to the following naming conventions:"
msgstr ""

# 7f2bb4f0dfe842fd9a3c7d827b5c3d11
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:92
msgid ""
"The TS prefix is used for all function and variable names defined in the "
"Traffic Server API. For example, :data:`TS_EVENT_NONE`, :type:`TSMutex`, "
"and :func:`TSContCreate`."
msgstr ""

# 490c7d734e1e4142bed772eb600007bd
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:96
msgid ""
"Enumerated values are always written in all uppercase letters. For "
"example, :data:`TS_EVENT_NONE` and :data:`TS_VC_CLOSE_ABORT`."
msgstr ""

# ed0b6c26b56f4ede9c3abdb26320a803
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:99
msgid ""
"Constant values are all uppercase; enumerated values can be seen as a "
"subset of constants. For example, :data:`TS_URL_SCHEME_FILE` and "
":data:`TS_MIME_FIELD_ACCEPT`."
msgstr ""

# e945dfaf0b4342e188757c041d84b6d6
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:103
msgid ""
"The names of defined types are mixed-case. For example, :type:`TSHttpSsn`"
" and :func:`TSHttpTxn`. :func:`TSDebug`"
msgstr ""

# 1fc6a03b532b488d89476729121fe58d
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:106
msgid ""
"Function names are mixed-case. For example, :func:`TSUrlCreate` and "
":func:`TSContDestroy`."
msgstr ""

# 810583c82c694817a515a2e9a12b5f37
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:109
msgid ""
"Function names use the following subject-verb naming style: "
"TS-<subject>-<verb>, where <subject> goes from general to specific. This "
"makes it easier to determine what a function does by reading its name. "
"For example, the function to retrieve the password field (the specific "
"subject) from a URL (the general subject) is :func:`TSUrlPasswordGet`."
msgstr ""

# ba4f35cc5493466aaa24d11aa7e484c8
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:116
msgid ""
"Common verbs like Create, Destroy, Get, Set, Copy, Find, Retrieve, "
"Insert, Remove, and Delete are used only when appropriate."
msgstr ""

# f0b0bc9328c44922a1d748d299a3f0b0
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:122
msgid "Plugin Loading and Configuration"
msgstr ""

# c21e5a39efc44e8c9258548f0098dd19
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:124
msgid ""
"When Traffic Server is first started, it consults the plugin.config file "
"to determine the names of all shared plugin libraries that need to be "
"loaded. The plugin.config file also defines arguments that are to be "
"passed to each plugin's initialization function, :func:`TSPluginInit`. "
"The :file:`records.config` file defines the path to each plugin shared "
"library."
msgstr ""

# 150aa07816834082b479dddadf18bdc4
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:131
msgid ""
"The sample :file:`plugin.config` file below contains a comment line, a "
"blank line, and two plugin configurations::"
msgstr ""

# 0807ebb782f14bd0aa033a2e5f241188
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:138
msgid ""
"Each plugin configuration in the :file:`plugin.config` file resembles a "
"UNIX or DOS shell command; each line in :file:`plugin.config` cannot "
"exceed 1023 characters."
msgstr ""

# 9ebaa95a7ba346ba8f81644530e00e25
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:142
msgid ""
"The first plugin configuration is for a plugin named my-plugin.so. It "
"contains three arguments that are to be passed to that plugin's "
"initialization routine. The second configuration is for a plugin named "
"some-plugin.so; it contains three arguments. The last argument, "
"$proxy.config.http.cache.on, is actually a configuration variable. "
"Traffic Server will look up the specified configuration variable and "
"substitute its value."
msgstr ""

# d18a10daa960470794d9f4ebc0bba594
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:150
msgid ""
"Plugins are loaded and initialized by Traffic Server in the order they "
"appear in the :file:`plugin.config` file."
msgstr ""

# ddbc726f5701439aa9e517a2aea277e8
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:156
msgid "Plugin Initialization"
msgstr ""

# c4ef2b6c87764d9cac04f12274a0af39
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSAPI.en.rst:158
msgid ""
"Each plugin must define an initialization function named "
":func:`TSPluginInit` that Traffic Server invokes when the plugin is "
"loaded. :func:`TSPluginInit` is commonly used to read configuration "
"information and register hooks for event notification."
msgstr ""

